Our mission is to bring every youth in social mainstream and transform them into fruitful resources of future." Every year, we reach thousands of youths in both rural and urban areas through a range of interventions. Our programs include post-school education, mainstreaming out of education youths, providing learning support to both in-collage and out of collage students, providing students the access to books, research and analysis, protecting vulnerable youths among others. Senior team members are a part of several policy making bodies both at the Central and State levels.Shri Shiv Shakti Shikshan Sansthan is the largest non-governmental organization working to provide quality vocational education to the underprivileged youths of India. Shri Shiv Shakti Shikshan Sansthan was established in 2010 to provide post-school education to the students in the slums of Sardarshahar. Since then, the organization has grown both in scope and geographical coverage. Their programs are designed to ensure that: 1. Enrollment in various jobs increases. 2. Learning in collages and communities increases. 3. The education network reaches to the students who are unable to afford tuition or coaching fees. 4. Models are replicated and scaled up to serve large numbers of youths to achieve a large scale impact.
